[
    {
        "content": "<p>At Firely, we are currently planning to implement a component which can transform a mapping file containing FHIR mapping language rules to a StructureMap. The initial idea would be to use $convert for this task. Any suggestions on what the Content-Type would look like for the input parameter, i.e. a mapping language file?</p>",
        "id": 160468932,
        "sender_full_name": "Alexander Zautke",
        "timestamp": 1552302183
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Or would the first sentence under <a href=\"https://www.hl7.org/fhir/mapping-language.html#syntax\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"https://www.hl7.org/fhir/mapping-language.html#syntax\">\"General Syntax Notes\"</a> indicate that the content-type should be \"text/plain\" and you would need try to parse the content to see if it actually contains mapping language rules?</p>",
        "id": 160602428,
        "sender_full_name": "Alexander Zautke",
        "timestamp": 1552419279
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>interesting question. I've not considered about a mime type for that language. I'd guess at something like text/x-fhir-mapping</p>",
        "id": 160748872,
        "sender_full_name": "Grahame Grieve",
        "timestamp": 1552535090
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Not sure it meets the requirements of \"text\"...</p>",
        "id": 160750981,
        "sender_full_name": "Lloyd McKenzie",
        "timestamp": 1552538453
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>it certainly does. It's UTF-8 text</p>",
        "id": 160751791,
        "sender_full_name": "Grahame Grieve",
        "timestamp": 1552539567
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I thought text had to be something intended to be read by a human</p>",
        "id": 160752221,
        "sender_full_name": "Lloyd McKenzie",
        "timestamp": 1552540092
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>that's exactly what it is</p>",
        "id": 160753491,
        "sender_full_name": "Grahame Grieve",
        "timestamp": 1552541942
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>You have a different idea of 'human' than I do I guess...</p>",
        "id": 160753503,
        "sender_full_name": "Lloyd McKenzie",
        "timestamp": 1552541975
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>we're talking about this format:</p>",
        "id": 160753553,
        "sender_full_name": "Grahame Grieve",
        "timestamp": 1552542029
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><a href=\"http://hl7.org/fhir/account-version-maps.html\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"http://hl7.org/fhir/account-version-maps.html\">http://hl7.org/fhir/account-version-maps.html</a></p>",
        "id": 160753572,
        "sender_full_name": "Grahame Grieve",
        "timestamp": 1552542070
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>In <a href=\"https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc2046#section-4.1\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc2046#section-4.1\">RFC 2046</a>, defining the characteristics of a <code>text/*</code> subtype, there is no requirement that  the format needs to be human readable. It only needs to be \"principally textual in form\". If we have a look at all registered <a href=\"https://www.iana.org/assignments/media-types/media-types.xhtml#text\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"https://www.iana.org/assignments/media-types/media-types.xhtml#text\">IANA media types</a>, there is no other format having a \"*-\" prefix. Because of this, I would prefer \"text/fhir-mapping\".</p>",
        "id": 161036600,
        "sender_full_name": "Alexander Zautke",
        "timestamp": 1552894082
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>To conform to <a href=\"https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc6657#page-3\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc6657#page-3\">New Rules for Default \"charset\" Parameter Values for <code>text/*</code> Media\n    Types - RFC6657</a>, the correct way of identifying a mapping language file would then be 'text/fhir-mapping; charset=utf-8'</p>",
        "id": 161037168,
        "sender_full_name": "Alexander Zautke",
        "timestamp": 1552894935
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>ok</p>",
        "id": 161088007,
        "sender_full_name": "Grahame Grieve",
        "timestamp": 1552936950
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>want to make a task so we remember this?</p>",
        "id": 161088016,
        "sender_full_name": "Grahame Grieve",
        "timestamp": 1552936960
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Added <a href=\"https://gforge.hl7.org/gf/project/fhir/tracker/?action=TrackerItemEdit&amp;tracker_item_id=20577\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"https://gforge.hl7.org/gf/project/fhir/tracker/?action=TrackerItemEdit&amp;tracker_item_id=20577\">Gforge 20577</a></p>",
        "id": 161331486,
        "sender_full_name": "Alexander Zautke",
        "timestamp": 1553163010
    }
]